questions.text:
forEach natijasi qanday bo‘ladi?
```js
const arr = [1, 2, 3];
const res = arr.forEach(x => x * 2);
console.log(res, arr);
```

map qanday natija qaytaradi?
```js
const arr = [1, 2, 3];
const r = arr.map(x => x * 2);
console.log(r[1], arr.length);
```

filter bilan juft elementlar soni nechta?
```js
const a = [1, 2, 3, 4];
const even = a.filter(x => x % 2 === 0);
console.log(even.length);
```

Bo‘sh massivda every qanday ishlaydi?
```js
const ok = [].every(x => x > 0);
console.log(ok);
```

some natijasi nima bo‘ladi?
```js
const a = [1, 3, 5];
const ok = a.some(x => x % 2 === 0);
console.log(ok);
```

includes va NaN munosabati?
```js
const a = [NaN];
console.log(a.includes(NaN));
```

forEach ichida o‘zgartirish va qaytish qiymati:
```js
const a = [1, 2];
const r = a.forEach((v, i) => { a[i] = v * 2; });
console.log(r, a);
```

filter(Boolean) nimani qiladi?
```js
const ids = [0, 1, 2, 3];
const r = ids.filter(Boolean);
console.log(r);
```

includes ning manfiy fromIndex bilan ishlashi:
```js
const arr = ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd'];
console.log(arr.includes('b', -2));
```

every va tur tekshirish:
```js
const arr = [1, 2, '3'];
const ok = arr.every(x => typeof x === 'number');
console.log(ok);
```

Bo‘sh massivda some qanday ishlaydi?
```js
const ok = [].some(x => x > 0);
console.log(ok);
```

new Array(3).map() hatti-harakati:
```js
const a = new Array(3);
const b = a.map((x, i) => i);
console.log(b.length, b[0]);
```

filter asl massivni o‘zgartiradimi?
```js
const a = [1, 2, 3];
const b = a.filter(x => x > 1);
console.log(a, b);
```

includes va obyektlar (taqqoslash bo‘yicha):
```js
const x = { id: 1 };
const arr = [{ id: 1 }, x];
console.log(arr.includes({ id: 1 }));
```

forEach ichida return erta to‘xtatadimi?
```js
let sum = 0;
[1, 2, 3, 4].forEach(n => {
  if (n > 2) return;
  sum += n;
});
console.log(sum);
```

Zanjirlash: map → filter → indeks:
```js
const r = [1, 2, 3].map(x => x * 2).filter(x => x > 3)[0];
console.log(r);
```

every birinchi mos kelmagan joyda to‘xtaydimi?
```js
const arr = [2, 4, 5, 6];
const ok = arr.every(x => x % 2 === 0);
console.log(ok);
```

some erta to‘xtashi (sanash):
```js
const arr = [10, 20, 30, 5, 40];
let count = 0;
arr.some(x => {
  count++;
  return x < 10;
});
console.log(count);
```

map + every kombinatsiyasi:
```js
const a = ['1', '2', '3'];
const ok = a.map(Number).every(n => typeof n === 'number');
console.log(ok);
```

filter ichida asl massivni o‘zgartirish:
```js
let a = [1, 2, 3, 4];
const b = a.filter((x, i) => {
  a[i] = x * 10;
  return x % 2 === 0;
});
console.log(a, b);
```

some satr uzunligidan foydalanganda:
```js
const s = ['a', 'bb', 'ccc'];
console.log(s.some(x => x.length === 2));
```

every va Boolean:
```js
const a = ['', ' '];
console.log(a.every(Boolean));
```

forEach davomida push qilish ta’siri:
```js
let a = [1, 2, 3];
a.forEach((v, i) => {
  if (i === 0) a.push(4);
  a[i] = v * 2;
});
console.log(a.length);
```

map va obyektlarni ko‘chirish:
```js
const users = [{ id: 1 }, { id: 2 }];
const copies = users.map(u => ({ ...u }));
copies[0].id = 99;
console.log(users[0].id);
```

filter va tur konversiyasi:
```js
const arr = [1, 2, 3];
console.log(arr.filter(x => x > '2'));
```

Kombinatsiya: every + some + includes:
```js
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 4];
const ok = arr.every(n => n > 0) && arr.some(n => n > 3) && arr.includes(2);
console.log(ok);
```
